      "cve": "CVE-2018-13812",
      "cwe": {
        "id": "CWE-22",
        "name": "Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')"
      },
      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "A directory traversal vulnerability has been identified that could enable download of arbitrary files from the device. The security vulnerability could be exploited by an attacker with network access to the integrated web server.\u00a0CVE-2018-13812 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.5 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N).",
          "title": "Vulnerability Summary"
        }
